## Phase 2 -- Environment Setup

### Conda Environment

```shell
conda create -n ReMindRag python==3.13.2
conda activate ReMindRag
pip install -r requirements.txt --extra-index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu126
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `--extra-index-url` flag is **required** -- CUDA 12.6 PyTorch wheels are hosted on PyTorch's server, not PyPI.

### Dockerfile (Created)

[Dockerfile](file:///c:/Users/mtuan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ReMindRAG/Dockerfile) -- Multi-stage build:
- **Stage 1 (builder):** Installs all pip packages with build tools
- **Stage 2 (runtime):** Copies only site-packages, no compilers
- Pre-downloads NLTK `punkt_tab` data
- Pre-creates all runtime directories
- Filters out Windows-only packages automatically

### .dockerignore (Created)

[.dockerignore](file:///c:/Users/mtuan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ReMindRAG/.dockerignore) -- Excludes `Rag_Cache/`, `venv/`, `model_cache/`, `__pycache__/` to prevent stale data and reduce image size.

### Dependency Pinning

All 146 packages version-pinned in `requirements.txt`. `requirements_repro.txt` re-encoded from UTF-16 to UTF-8 (was unreadable by pip).

---

## Phase 3 -- Credential & External Dependency Detection

### API Keys Required

| Service | Config Location | Required? |
|---------|----------------|-----------|
| OpenAI API | `api_key.json` (`base_url` + `api_key`) | Yes -- for real inference |
| HuggingFace Hub | `HF_TOKEN` env var or `huggingface-cli login` | Yes -- for model downloads |

### External Services

| Service | Usage | Offline Capable? |
|---------|-------|------------------|
| OpenAI API | Entity extraction, answer generation, answer checking | No -- requires live API |
| HuggingFace Hub | Model download (`nomic-embed-text-v2-moe`) | Yes, after first download (cached locally) |
| ChromaDB | Local persistent vector store | Yes -- fully local |

### Can This Run Offline?

**Partially.** After initial model download, only the LLM inference requires network. The embedding model, ChromaDB, and KG construction all run locally.

### Estimated API Cost

| Operation | Model | Est. tokens/call | Calls per doc | Cost |
|-----------|-------|-------------------|---------------|------|
| Entity extraction | gpt-4o-mini | ~2K | 1 per chunk | ~$0.001/chunk |
| Answer generation | gpt-4o-mini | ~3K | 1 per query | ~$0.002/query |
| Judge (rewrite) | gpt-4o | ~1K | 1 per eval Q | ~$0.01/question |
| Judge (check) | gpt-4o | ~500 | 1 per eval Q | ~$0.005/question |

**Full LooGLE eval (20 titles, ~100 questions):** ~$2-5 USD

---

## Phase 4 -- Hardware & Resource Analysis

### GPU Requirement

**Optional.** GPU accelerates embedding computation but is not required.

### CUDA / Device Usage

| File | Usage | Fallback |
|------|-------|----------|
| `embeddings/hg_sentence_transformers.py` | `torch.cuda.is_available()` auto-detection | CPU fallback built-in |
| `eval/eval_LooGLE.py` | `set_seed()` configures `cuda.manual_seed_all` | Only if GPU available |

### VRAM Estimate

| Model | Parameters | Est. VRAM |
|-------|-----------|-----------|
| nomic-embed-text-v2-moe | ~137M (MoE) | ~1 GB FP32 |
| all-MiniLM-L6-v2 (test) | ~22M | ~100 MB |

### CPU-Only Mode

Works automatically -- `torch.cuda.is_available()` returns `False` on CPU-only systems and all code paths handle this.

---

## Phase 5 -- Data & Artifact Verification

### Required Datasets

| Dataset | Source | Location | Auto-download? |
|---------|--------|----------|----------------|
| LooGLE | HuggingFace `bigai-nlco/LooGLE` | `eval/dataset_cache/` | Yes |
| LooGLE preprocessed | Google Drive zip | `eval/dataset_cache/LooGLE-rewrite-data/` | No -- manual |
| HotpotQA | Local JSON files | `eval/dataset_cache/Hotpot/` | No -- manual |
| Example data | In-repo | `example/example_data.txt` | Included |

### Hard-coded Directories (Fixed)

| Original | Fixed To |
|----------|----------|
| `save_dir + "/chroma_data"` | `os.path.join(save_dir, "chroma_data")` |
| `save_dir + "/model_cache"` | `os.path.join(save_dir, "model_cache")` |
| `sys.path.append('../')` | `EVAL_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))` |
| `"../api_key.json"` | `os.path.join(REPO_ROOT, 'api_key.json')` |

### Smoke Test Data

`repro_test.py` uses `MockAgent` + `example_data.txt` -- no API key needed, validates full pipeline.

